node.text: Hailing from Provence and named for the region's popular terra-cotta dishes, tian is a combination of summer vegetables perfumed with olive oil and thyme and crusted with Gruyère cheese. Get our Zucchini and Tomato Tian with Caramelized Onions (Tian de Courgettes aux Tomates) recipe by clicking the link in our profile.

node.text: Learn how to make easy grilled potatoes from our Five Ingredient Dinners cookbook! 🥔🔥

node.text: Chicken schnitzel is defined by thin, tender, juicy cutlets coated in a fine, wrinkly crust that puffs away from the meat during frying. Get our recipe by clicking the link in our profile.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on July 21, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and food.

node.text: Our Blueberry Grunt recipe produces juicy berries topped with biscuity dumplings. The best part? There's no need to turn on the oven. Recipe link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on July 21, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: You can use that leftover pickling brine in your fridge to create the easiest creamy dressing. Get our method from our Five Ingredient Dinners cookbook by clicking the link in our profile.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by America's Test Kitchen on July 21, 2021 tagging @elle_simone_scott, and @patijinich. May be an image of 1 person and text.

node.text: New episode of The Walk-In! @patijinich, a Mexican chef, TV personality, cookbook author, educator, and food writer, joins @elle_simone_scott in the Walk-In. Listen now wherever you get your podcasts.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on July 21, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: For a delicious summer vegetable sandwich, we kept the focus on fresh summer vegetables by pairing tender mesclun with zucchini and mint. Get our French Summer Sandwiches with Zucchini and Olive Tapenade recipe by clicking the link in our profile.
